            "body": "> Did you really mean what you wrote in the examples? Neither of them is correct code.\r\nI don't know what you mean. The following compiles on my machine\r\n```\r\ncdef class MyClass:\r\n    pass\r\ncdef func:\r\n    pass\r\ncpdef func:\r\n    pass\r\n```\r\n> Note that the Emacs Cython mode has not seen any maintenance in some years. We take PRs if we get them, but otherwise, it lacks a maintainer currently.\r\n\r\nI thought that you would say that. In this case, I suggest leaving this issue open until someone finds the time to fix it.\r\nI think that's not the only code in Cython that lacks a maintainer.\r\n\r\n\\*Insert rant about lacking open source maintainers here.\\*",
