        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Here's [an email](https://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/bug-gnu-emacs/2015-02/msg00679.html) explaining how to fix this problem by modifying python.el. I'm not sure if there's a fix that could made in cython-mode that would accomplish the same thing without requiring an upstream change.\r\n\r\nSpecifically, you need modify the `block-start`, `dedenter`, and `defun` entries in the `python-rx-constituents` alist in python.el. Here's how mine looks:\r\n\r\n```\r\n;;; Python specialized rx\r\n\r\n(eval-and-compile\r\n  (defconst python-rx-constituents\r\n    `((block-start          . ,(rx symbol-start\r\n                                   (or \"def\" \"class\" \"if\" \"elif\" \"else\" \"try\"\r\n                                       \"except\" \"finally\" \"for\" \"while\" \"with\"\r\n                                       ;; Python 3.5+ PEP492\r\n                                       (and \"async\" (+ space)\r\n                                            (or \"def\" \"for\" \"with\"))\r\n                                       ;; Cython\r\n                                       \"cdef\" \"cpdef\" \"enum\" \"struct\"\r\n                                       \"union\" \"IF\" \"ELIF\" \"ELSE\")\r\n                                   symbol-end))\r\n      (dedenter            . ,(rx symbol-start\r\n                                  (or \"elif\" \"else\" \"except\" \"finally\" \"ELIF\"\r\n                                      \"ELSE\")\r\n                                   symbol-end))\r\n      (block-ender         . ,(rx symbol-start\r\n                                  (or\r\n                                   \"break\" \"continue\" \"pass\" \"raise\" \"return\")\r\n                                  symbol-end))\r\n      (decorator            . ,(rx line-start (* space) ?@ (any letter ?_)\r\n                                   (* (any word ?_))))\r\n      (defun                . ,(rx symbol-start\r\n                                   (or \"def\" \"class\"\r\n                                       ;; Python 3.5+ PEP492\r\n                                       (and \"async\" (+ space) \"def\")\r\n                                       ;; Cython\r\n                                       \"cdef\" \"cpdef\")\r\n                                   symbol-end))\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\nWith these changes, cython-mode works fine for me.",
